{"name": "ploosh", "metadata": {"name": "ploosh", "version": "0.2.27", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/CSharplie/ploosh/", "license": "Apache License 2.0", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/CSharplie/ploosh", "dependencies": ["pyodbc", "pymysql", "pg8000", "snowflake-sqlalchemy", "databricks-sql-connector", "sqlalchemy-bigquery", "google-cloud-bigquery-storage", "pandas-gbq", "pydata-google-auth", "colorama", "PyYAML", "Pyjeb", "numpy", "pandas", "openpyxl", "sqlalchemy", "pyspark"], "summary": "A framework to automatize your tests for data projects", "upload_time": 1732912520}, "documentation": ["# Ploosh\n\nPloosh is yaml based framework used to automatized the testing process in data projects. \n\n# Get started\nGo to the [ploosh wiki](https://github.com/CSharplie/ploosh/wiki) to find the get started tutorial.\n\n## Steps\n1. Install ploosh package\n2. Run tests\n3. Analyse results\n\n## Install Ploosh\n\nInstall from [PyPi](https://pypi.org/project/ploosh/) package manager:\n``` shell\npip install ploosh\n```\n\n## Run tests\n``` shell\nploosh --connections \"connections.yml\" --cases \"test_cases\" --export \"JSON\" --p_my_sql_server_password \"mypassword\"\n```\n\n![Execution result](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wiki/CSharplie/ploosh/images/execution.png)\n\n## Test results\n``` json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Test aggregated data\",\n    \"state\": \"passed\",\n    \"source\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 0.0032982\n    },\n    \"expected\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 6.0933333333333335e-05\n    },\n    \"compare\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 0.00046468333333333334\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"Test unvalid data\",\n    \"state\": \"failed\",\n    \"source\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 0.00178865\n    },\n    \"expected\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 1.49e-05\n    },\n    \"compare\": {\n      \"start\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"end\": \"2024-02-05T17:08:36Z\",\n      \"duration\": 1.8333333333333333e-07\n    },\n    \"error\": {\n      \"type\": \"count\",\n      \"message\": \"The count in source dataset (55) is differant than the count the in expected dataset (0)\"\n    }\n  }\n]\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter", "documentation": ["Test result exporter", "pylint: disable=R0903,W0613"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter.Exporter", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter.Exporter.date_to_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert datetime to string in ISO 8601 format"]}, {"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter.Exporter.export", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cases", "type": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Export test case results to the destination"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter.Exporter.name", "type": null, "documentation": ["Name of the exporter"]}, {"name": "ploosh.exporters.exporter.Exporter.output_path", "type": null, "documentation": ["Output path for the exported results"]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Test result exporter"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "ploosh.configuration", "documentation": ["Module to manage the configuration of the framework"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ploosh.configuration.Configuration", "bas